==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sphene
<hw>Sphene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sph⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>sfh`n</grk> a wedge.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral found usually in thin, wedge-shaped
crystals of a yellow or green to black color. It is a silicate of
titanium and calcium; titanite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sphenethmoid</ent>⟦br⟧
